## 🔑 Key Requirements

### 1. REST API Endpoints

| Prefix | Layer | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `/api/v1/identity/*` | Layer 0 | Register, verify, get reputation |
| `/api/v1/catalog/*` | Layer 1 | CRUD products, federated search |
| `/api/v1/orders/*` | Layer 2 | Create, pay, track, complete orders |
| `/api/v1/logistics/*` | Layer 3 | Register providers, submit quotes, track shipments |
| `/api/v1/trust/*` | Layer 4 | File disputes, submit evidence, rate transactions |
| `/api/v1/governance/*` | Layer 6 | Submit proposals, vote, check parameters |

### 2. Authentication & Security

- JWT tokens for client authentication
- API keys for server-to-server calls
- Rate limiting: 100 requests/hour per client
- Sandbox mode for testing (separate credentials)

### 3. Real-Time Events (WebSocket)

```typescript
client.on('order:created', (payload) => { ... })
client.on('shipment:updated', (payload) => { ... })
client.on('dispute:opened', (payload) => { ... })
client.on('proposal:submitted', (payload) => { ... })
```

**Event types:**

| Event | Trigger |
|---|---|
| `identity:verified` | KYC verification complete |
| `product:created` | New product listed |
| `order:created` | Order placed |
| `order:paid` | Payment confirmed |
| `order:delivered` | Delivery confirmed |
| `order:completed` | Order closed |
| `shipment:updated` | Tracking status change |
| `dispute:opened` | Dispute filed |
| `dispute:resolved` | Dispute concluded |
| `proposal:submitted` | Governance proposal created |
| `vote:cast` | Vote recorded |

### 4. Type Safety

- All requests/responses strictly typed
- Aligned with Supabase database schema
- Zod for runtime validation

### 5. Error Handling

Standard HTTP status codes with consistent error response format:

```typescript
{
  error: {
    code: "INVALID_ORDER_STATUS",
    message: "Cannot ship order in pending status",
    details: { ... }
  }
}
```

